    "en": {
      "title": "Examination for Korean fishing jobs begins",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The issuance of applications for the Korean language test for jobs in the fisheries sector in South Korea will be done online from 22.08.2022 to 26.08.2022.",
        "A passport is mandatory for applying for this examination, and a special method has been introduced by the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau based on the agreement of the Immigration Department for applicants who have not yet obtained it.",
        "Accordingly, the provincial offices of the Bureau will issue relevant letters of recommendation for such job seekers on August 15, 16 and 17, 2022. In order to obtain these letters of recommendation, the amount of Rs.10,109 charged as examination fee should be paid directly to the concerned office.",
        "By submitting the letter of recommendation to the head office of the Immigration Department at Battaramulla, the passport can be obtained through the one-day service.",
        "This is not applicable for the candidates who have already obtained their flight permits and they can apply for the examination through online mode by scanning and forwarding the examination fee paid application form. More information about this examination can be obtained from the official website of the bureau www.slbfe.lk."
      ],
